<div class='main section' id='main' name='Principal'><div class='widget Blog' data-version='1' id='Blog1'>
<div class='blog-posts hfeed'>

          <div class="date-outer">
        
<h2 class='date-header'><span>dilluns, 22 de juny de 2020</span></h2>

          <div class="date-posts">
        
<div class='post-outer'>
<div class='post hentry uncustomized-post-template' itemprop='blogPost' itemscope='itemscope' itemtype='http://schema.org/BlogPosting'>
<meta content='https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-WyUM6Vwvkmc/Xuxtjfi3PWI/AAAAAAAASo8/DZderVbD7sE-f0jKmk6GzIvxVpFD9cLZACLcBGAsYHQ/s640/BB10cOD.jpg' itemprop='image_url'/>
<meta content='2276589581319134606' itemprop='blogId'/>
<meta content='3867137123240190707' itemprop='postId'/>
<a name='3867137123240190707'></a>
<h3 class='post-title entry-title' itemprop='name'>
<a href='https://angelfalques.blogspot.com/2020/06/slaverys-shameful-legacy.html'>Slavery's shameful legacy.</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header'>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-body entry-content' id='post-body-3867137123240190707' itemprop='articleBody'>
<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;"><tbody>
<tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-WyUM6Vwvkmc/Xuxtjfi3PWI/AAAAAAAASo8/DZderVbD7sE-f0jKmk6GzIvxVpFD9cLZACLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/BB10cOD.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" data-original-height="454" data-original-width="634" height="458" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-WyUM6Vwvkmc/Xuxtjfi3PWI/AAAAAAAASo8/DZderVbD7sE-f0jKmk6GzIvxVpFD9cLZACLcBGAsYHQ/s640/BB10cOD.jpg" width="640" /></a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;"><span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; caption-side: bottom; color: #666666; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 1.384; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><b>An illustration showing slaves on board a slave ship.&nbsp;When the British government abolished slavery in 1833, around 47,000 individuals were compensated for the 'property' they had lost
</b></span></td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<span style="font-size: x-small;"></span><div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The debt was only paid back in 2015. Academics at University College London have created a database which tracks the slave-owners who benefited.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Many of them had links to or founded some of the UK's biggest companies including Greene King, P&amp;O, RSA Insurance, Barclays and even the Bank of England.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The sums paid out are not to be sneezed at: Benjamin Greene, founder of the Greene King brewery and pubs chain, was granted nearly &#163;500,000 in today's money when he surrendered rights to three plantations in the West Indies.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Simon Fraser, one of the founder members of the Lloyd's of London insurance market, was given nearly &#163;400,000 to surrender an estate in Dominica.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The Bank of England apologised for its part in the kidnapping and transportation of thousands of slaves, promising to remove portraits of those involved in this 'unacceptable part of English history'.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Greene King and Lloyd's of London were also quick to apologise for their past role in the slave trade after news of their links were published.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
They have offered to make amends for their slave legacy, saying they will fund projects to help black and other ethnic minorities. They are right to do so, and to have reacted so promptly.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Cynics might say they did so to avoid any damage done to the brand if those same protesters who have been pulling down statues of slave-owners were to boycott their pints or insurance services.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
That view seems unfair. Greene King's boss, Nick Mackenzie, sounded genuinely mortified by the brewery's 'inexcusable' past.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
More pertinently &#8211; and more importantly for future generations &#8211; he said the company's website would be updated to include the history of its slave-owner founder.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Similar contrition has been shown by Lloyd's of London, and the insurer will also be contributing to charities. But the banks, which also have links to the slave trade &#8211; Lloyds, RBS, HSBC and Barclays &#8211; have yet to comment on the UCL report.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Many will question where this thirst for raking over history will take us. Should every company in Britain, which was in existence at the relevant time, go through its archive to see what lies buried?</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
There are all manner of skeletons they would prefer did not come rattling out of the cupboard. The fortunes of many of our Victorian ancestors were built on the labour of women and children in the workhouses of the industrial revolution. Should their relatives be compensated?</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">And what about recent transgressions?</strong></strong></div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The list of corporates with dodgy not-so-distant pasts is long: clothing giants that make their fortunes from sweat-factories in Asia, banks such as HSBC laundering money for Mexican drug lords, or Standard Chartered channelling funds for Hezbollah.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Should they pay back their victims &#8211; assuming they can be identified?</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Will there be boycotts as there was of Barclays in the 1980s over apartheid in South Africa? What about buying oil from rich Middle Eastern states which didn't stop slavery until the 1960s?&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
When people drive their Porsche, do they worry about the Nazi past of its founder? These are delicate issues.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
This is not a cop-out but one way for firms to look at the past is to identify whether there are direct victims, or heirs to those victims. If so, make reparations to them.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
If Lloyd's and Greene King, now owned by Hong Kong's richest man Li Ka-Shing, want to give something back, that's good.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
What is of more importance is that they spend their charity money wisely on those who are truly disadvantaged.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The cash should go to help those who face barriers to opportunity because of race and because of deprivation. Otherwise, companies should apologise and move on.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Signs of a bounce</strong></div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The Bank of England has moved quickly to pump an extra &#163;100billion into the economy after April's shocking GDP numbers, the biggest one month drop on record.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Policymakers voted 8-1 to increase the size of the bond-buying programme but also to keep interest rates at a record low of 0.1 per cent.</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
It would be silly to be too cheerful but the Bank also said the latest demand numbers are not quite as 'negative' as expected.&nbsp;</div>
<div class="mol-para-with-font" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Translated into ordinary lingo, that sounds like the Brits have rediscovered shopping again and spending figures for May and June look better than could possibly be hoped for.</div>
<b></b><i></i><u></u><sub></sub><sup></sup><strike></strike><br />
<div style='clear: both;'></div>
