<h2 class='date-header'><span>diumenge, 21 de juny de 2020</span></h2>

          <div class="date-posts">
        
<div class='post-outer'>
<div class='post hentry uncustomized-post-template' itemprop='blogPost' itemscope='itemscope' itemtype='http://schema.org/BlogPosting'>
<meta content='https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-kl0rnt71pPQ/XuutL0QPJyI/AAAAAAAASog/gEFXdq3K5AY26e7iR2_wO0STfDxWCwDIgCLcBGAsYHQ/s640/BB15FSmd.jpg' itemprop='image_url'/>
<meta content='2276589581319134606' itemprop='blogId'/>
<meta content='9143604956933628774' itemprop='postId'/>
<a name='9143604956933628774'></a>
<h3 class='post-title entry-title' itemprop='name'>
<a href='https://angelfalques.blogspot.com/2020/06/the-australian-book-youve-finally-got.html'>The Australian book you've finally got time for: The Middle Parts of Fortune by Frederic Manning</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header'>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-body entry-content' id='post-body-9143604956933628774' itemprop='articleBody'>
<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;"><tbody>
<tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-kl0rnt71pPQ/XuutL0QPJyI/AAAAAAAASog/gEFXdq3K5AY26e7iR2_wO0STfDxWCwDIgCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/BB15FSmd.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" data-original-height="479" data-original-width="799" height="382" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-kl0rnt71pPQ/XuutL0QPJyI/AAAAAAAASog/gEFXdq3K5AY26e7iR2_wO0STfDxWCwDIgCLcBGAsYHQ/s640/BB15FSmd.jpg" width="640" /></a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;"><span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; caption-side: bottom; color: #666666; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 1.384; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;"><b>
 Soldiers climbing over their trench on the first day of the Battle of the Somme, 1 July, 1916.
</b></span></td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Why hasn&#8217;t Anzackery&#8217;s ever-rising tide washed Frederic Manning and The Middle Parts of Fortune further up the Australian literary shore?</div>
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span><br />
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Every Father&#8217;s Day and every Christmas publishers search, with increasing desperation, for fresh presentations of the Australian Great War experience. On that basis, one might have expected a combat novel lauded by Ernest Hemingway, TS Eliot, Ezra Pound, TE Lawrence and other immortals to exert more of a cultural presence.</div>
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span><br />
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
But while Frederic Manning &#8220;revivals&#8221; have been announced ever since the 1960s, the canon invoked during Anzac season still somehow begins and ends with Wilfred Owen, Siegfried Sassoon, Robert Graves and, perhaps, Charles Bean.</div>
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span><br />
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The problem might be traced to Manning&#8217;s marked divergence from the rugged Digger archetype celebrated by Bean and his acolytes.</div>
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">     </span><br />
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The son of a wealthy Sydney financier, Frederic was always delicate and bookish. At the age of just 15, his parents allowed him to depart for England with his much-older tutor, the Reverend Arthur Galton &#8211; a man who&#8217;d once moved in the same Oxford circles as Oscar Wilde and Lord Alfred Douglas. Together, they moved into the tiny village of Lincolnshire, where they maintained an intense (but perhaps non-sexual) relationship that shaped the boy into a scholar-aesthete like his mentor.</div>
<a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-uHX1POGoAiQ/Xuut18484lI/AAAAAAAASoo/PQ4DX3PYljQpBGKWSWEdd5mq-l5hU8AywCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/record-australia-great-war-.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Biographer Verna Coleman describes Manning as &#8220;the Last Exquisite&#8221;, both because of the delicacy of his prose and because of a brittleness that prevented him from capitalising on his early literary success. By 1928, his peers regarded Manning as talented but strangely old-fashioned: a chain-smoking, semi-alcoholic asthmatic with a bad back and poor digestion, more attuned to the aestheticism of the 1890s than contemporary modernism, and congenitally incapable of completing a major work.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font: 2rem/3.2rem &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
But that year the publisher (and fellow veteran) Peter Davies urged Manning to write about his experiences on the Somme &#8211; and locked him in his apartment until he did so. Supposedly, Manning wrote his loosely-fictionalised account entirely without revision, with Davies forestalling procrastination by rushing each chapter from the typewriter straight to print.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font: 2rem/3.2rem &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The Middle Parts of Fortune appeared anonymously in a volume only available to subscribers, with a bowdlerised edition subsequently released to the public under the title Her Privates We (another reference to the bawdy passage in which Hamlet declares fortune &#8220;a strumpet&#8221;).</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font: 2rem/3.2rem &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The problem was language: rather unexpectedly Manning, the fastidious aesthete, had reproduced the genuine wartime vocabulary instead of the euphemisms to which other (more obviously transgressive) novelists resorted.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font: 2rem/3.2rem &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
</a><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-_XZ9B70-X8E/XuuutynZHWI/AAAAAAAASow/P3xVWCd07wopcldBMAYrNpzW4qXEAAZ0gCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/record-australia-great-war-.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="600" data-original-width="600" height="640" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-_XZ9B70-X8E/XuuutynZHWI/AAAAAAAASow/P3xVWCd07wopcldBMAYrNpzW4qXEAAZ0gCLcBGAsYHQ/s640/record-australia-great-war-.jpg" width="640" /></a><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-uHX1POGoAiQ/Xuut18484lI/AAAAAAAASoo/PQ4DX3PYljQpBGKWSWEdd5mq-l5hU8AywCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/record-australia-great-war-.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><span style="color: black;">As a result, today his book cuts through the distancing of time. We&#8217;re accustomed to thinking of our great-grandparents enduring the trenches with Edwardian stoicism. Manning&#8217;s characters, however, respond to gunfire and mud with F and C bombs, just as we would.</span></a></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Yet in other ways The Middle Parts of Fortune also conveys the deep gulf between now and then.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
It follows the experiences of a private called Bourne &#8211; an obvious surrogate for Manning &#8211; for a few months on the Somme and Ancre fronts.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Critics have praised the book for celebrating the ordinary soldier, largely because its protagonist stays in the ranks rather than accepting the commission to which his education suits him. Yet Manning portrays Bourne as more misfit than egalitarian, alienated from the English officers as an Australian who didn&#8217;t attend a public school, and separated from the other men by his erudition.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Indeed, isolation defines the war, an experience that, despite moments of camaraderie, every man endures in solitude.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
&#8220;One by one,&#8221; Manning writes, &#8220;they realised that each must go alone, and that each of them already was alone with himself, helping the others perhaps, but looking at them with strange eyes, while the world became unreal and empty, and they moved in a mystery, where no help was.&#8221;</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">     </span></div>
<blockquote style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
   <div style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">
The highly strung, deeply repressed man [was] always slightly out of kilter with his era</div>
</blockquote>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">    </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
It&#8217;s that profound atomisation, conveyed in Manning&#8217;s finely wrought prose, that makes the book&#8217;s brief and hallucinatory battle scenes so terrifying, with modern combat a sensory overload inflicted on the individual psyche.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Famously, Wilfred Owen describes his subject as &#8220;the pity of war&#8221;. Manning takes a very different approach.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
&#8220;To call [war] a crime against mankind,&#8221; he says in his introduction, &#8220;is to miss at least half its significance; it is also the punishment of a crime.&#8221;</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
Where militarists like Ernst Jünger show the conflict redeeming men through violence, Manning sees wartime suffering as facilitating a peculiar authenticity, as his characters &#8220;turn [&#8230;] from the wreckage and misery of life to an empty heaven and from an empty heaven to the silence of their own hearts&#8221;.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">     </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin: 0px 0px 1.9rem; orphans: 2; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-uHX1POGoAiQ/Xuut18484lI/AAAAAAAASoo/PQ4DX3PYljQpBGKWSWEdd5mq-l5hU8AywCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/record-australia-great-war-.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><span style="color: black;">The book is not, then, in any sense a pacifist or antiwar novel. The critic Arnold Bennett went so far as to describe it as &#8220;inspiring&#8221; because it &#8220;compels in the reader a reluctant belief that war is glorious after all.&#8221; But that&#8217;s not quite right either. After all, Manning describes heroism as &#8220;indistinguishable from despair&#8221;, an assertion that no militarist would make but one that reflects his almost existentialist preoccupation with the individual personality in extremis.</span></a></div>
<a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-uHX1POGoAiQ/Xuut18484lI/AAAAAAAASoo/PQ4DX3PYljQpBGKWSWEdd5mq-l5hU8AywCLcBGAsYHQ/s1600/record-australia-great-war-.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
We might go so far as to say that Manning&#8217;s war reflected Manning&#8217;s peace. The highly strung, deeply repressed man always slightly out of kilter with his era seems to have experienced the Battle of the Somme as an intensification, almost to the point of liberation, of the isolation he already felt.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
The final words of The Middle Parts of Fortune encapsulate the theme of one of the strangest, most compelling books from the Great War.</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
&#8220;They sat there silently,&#8221; the novel ends, &#8220;each man keeping his own secret.&#8221;</div>
<div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: white; color: #333333; display: inline !important; float: none; font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;,&quot;Segoe WP&quot;,&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;Sans-Serif&quot;; font-size: 2rem; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 3.2rem; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">  </span></div>
</a><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: &amp;quot; font-size: 20px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; margin-bottom: 1.9rem; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; orphans: 2; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px;">
<br /></div>
<div style='clear: both;'></div>
</div>
